entry.title: media/gpu/VP8VaapiVED: Specify a loop filter level by rate controller
entry.content:
Originally, we set the highest loop filter level, 63, all the time. It

causes inefficiency in compression; an encoder driver produces the

large chunk even for identical frames. We need to rather specify a

smaller loop filter level [1].

This CL specifies a loop filter level computed by a software rate

controller to each frame.



[1] Chapter 6. https://static.googleusercontent.com/media/research.google.com/ja//pubs/archive/37073.pdf

entry.title: Stop using a RenderWidgetHost observer in FileSelectHelper.
entry.content:
FileSelectHelper already observes RenderFrameDeleted and

RenderFrameHostChanged to clear its RenderFrameHost reference. This

means that the RenderWidgetHost observer, which is also used to clear

the RFH reference, is redundant, since it shouldn't be possible to

destroy a RFH's RWH without triggering destruction of the RFH itself.



This CL removes the RWH observation logic, since it is not only

redundant, but also incorrect for OOPIFs, since the RWH being observed

was retrieved from the frame's RenderViewHost, and that is not going

to be the right RWH for an OOPIF.



This CL also re-enables a test originally added for

https://crbug.com/621076, to ensure that there's no RFH UAF when a

subframe triggers a file chooser and is then destroyed by its parent.

The test was originally disabled due to (unrelated?) memory leak

failures on ASAN bots, but that issue appears to now be fixed, since

the test passes just fine on the ASAN bots.

entry.title: Introduce Spare Tab in Clank
entry.content:
In this CL, we add new method warmupManager.createSpareTab to create

a spare tab to speed up navigations involving creating a tab.



This triggers WebContents creation along with initializing tab,

web contents helpers. To allow callers take the spare Tab, we

implement warmupManager.takeSpareTab.



Building of this detached spare Tab is implemented in

ChromeTabCreator.buildDetachedSpareTab. Since this is experimental, we implement this new feature behind a feature flag SpareTab.



We also initialize the renderer with spare Tab creation. This is guarded with feature param.



Metrics: We add Android.SpareTab.FinalStatus to track the status of spare tab creation, deletion, and usage.



Testing: Tests are added to WarmupmanagerTest to verify the functionality of this spare tab creation, deletion, metrics etc.



We will be using spareTab for optimizations navigations from start surface in crrev.com/c/4348048.



Detailed design doc for spare tab optimization:

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1blqCc7W8oGNtKVn90yLJDYUWSqzoO03aE5tyk1CrWLM/edit?usp=sharing&resourcekey=0-qj1ZVcaqm2s3vOR2eEQqJA

entry.title: Create util API to retrieve view in root window by display + element ID.
entry.content:
Creates a util API to retrieve a view in a root window by display +

element ID. The API returns nullptr if no matches are found and does not

guarantee which match is returned in the event of multiple matches. The

lack of guarantee is due to lack of downstream guarantees from the

element tracker framework backing the API.



This util API will be reused in future CLs to ensure that help bubbles

in the Welcome Tour always show on the primary display. It will also be

used in the Holding Space Tour to show a help bubble over the shelf

instance on the same display as a wallpaper drag-and-drop event.

entry.title: Support multi-instance launch from LauncherShortcutActivity
entry.content:
This CL includes a fix to an issue where dragging the

launcher shortcut from the 12L task bar to open a

new window in split screen currently doesn't work because

FLAG_ACTIVITY_MULTIPLE_TASK is not preserved in the intent that is

launched. The fix includes the following updates:

1. Retain FLAG_ACTIVITY_MULTIPLE_TASK in LauncherShortcutActivity#onCreate if present in the original intent and if lesser than the supported max # of Chrome instances is open, before bouncing it off to ChromeLauncherActivity.

2. Retain FLAG_ACTIVITY_MULTIPLE_TASK in LauncherIntentDispatcher#dispatchToTabbedActivity if the intent source is Chrome, since this indicates an intention to support a multi-instance launch.



Demo: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1o5wMGxH-Uo0hKVBUoqAATXIu66fMa1t8/view?usp=sharing

entry.title: [android] Add framework for automatically reset fields after test runs
entry.content:
Whenever we have a static method on a production class of the type

setSomethingForTest(...) that is invoked only from tests, we still have

to remember to clean it up in every test that uses it (e.g. setting

the value back to null).



This has proven itself to be easy to forget, leading to issues with

our test infrastructure that can arise from unrelated CLs that change

how tests are sharded.



This CL adds a framework to make it simple to clean this up throughout

our code base by adding a registry that is used for automatic cleanup

for JUnit and Robolectric tests.



The CL also showcases how this is intented to be used by using it in

both JUnit and Roboletric tests.
